Program: The Documentary
Title: All That Stands in the Way - The Debate
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01z8mcx
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 25 May 2014
Ros Atkins brings three teenage girls from ‘All that Stands in The Way’ together in New York City with two other girls, for a unique debate on gender inequality. The group, which includes girls from London, Lesotho and Iceland meet media star Tina Brown and delegates at the Women in the World summit, for a conversation ranging from everyday sexism to the problems of balancing traditional attitudes with modern ambitions. Show less